reviews.review_text: It's a bit of a crowded place during pick time. And they have a limited sitting area, on the top. Snacks are good, Sabudhana vada is a new and good addition to the menu, tasty but a little oily.

A Disappointing Experience That Does Not Come Close to Fine Dining

Despite the label of “fine dining,” this restaurant misses the mark on several fronts, coming across as quite average. The upkeep and maintenance leave much to be desired; the condition of the restrooms, hand wash areas, and overall hygiene standards were notably lacking.

The restaurant is divided into separate vegetarian and non-vegetarian sections, but the vegetarian section is poorly designed. The air conditioning is insufficient for the space, making the central area uncomfortably warm.

The toilet in the non-veg section opens directly into the seating area and also there is an exposed hand wash station.

The seating arrangement is cramped, offering little to no privacy, which detracts from the dining experience.

The food itself was unremarkable, and the service was disappointing. There was no visible floor or restaurant manager overseeing the operations, which resulted in disorganized service and a lack of attention to detail.

Overall, dining here was a letdown and did not live up to expectations.
We went to their Madgaon outlet, had some great Goan breakfast. This is a good place to have a good vegetarian breakfast, especially try the bun potato Bhaji mushroom Bhaji and Puri.
